		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>mmc3 chr rom wiring</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />are there numerous ways to wire the chr rom on mmc3 repros?  most of the time i use the guide on this site, but sometimes i get garbled graphics.  all the pins are soldered and everything looks fine.  i have been looking through old posts and it seems some people wire the pin 1 to pin 32.  is this necessary?  any other pins that could be wired to fix the graphics?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Bregalad</b> [ Sat Apr 26, 2008 6:05 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />No there is only one correct way to wire the chip, at least when it comes to data/adress pins.
<br />When it comes to useless pins such as VPP, /PGM or such things wire them to VCC (pin 32) and you should be fine. If you get scrambled graphics you most likely did something wrong with the adress/data/control pins.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


